UC OSS 0.5.0 as a co-equal catalog binding: per-principal authz-gated, prefix-downscoped,
external-id-pinned credential vending. Proof, 2026-07-10.

Catalog: Unity Catalog OSS v0.5.0-SNAPSHOT (pinned commit 0f14452, tag v0.5.0-20260428-30037019),
built from source via open-lakehouse/unitycatalog-console. Server run with server.authorization=enable
(JCasbin). Two per-tenant principals (tenant_a, tenant_b), each granted READ FILES/CREATE EXTERNAL
TABLE/SELECT on ONLY its own external location. Per-user identity via internal-issuer RS256 JWTs
(the mechanism UC's own integration tests use).

Account redacted to <ACCT>; ephemeral STS keys and the UC-generated external-id redacted.

=========================================================================================
PART A. Per-principal authz gate (no AWS; H2 backend). Boot: unauth GET /catalogs -> 401;
admin -> 200; server.authorization=enable. The temporary-path-credentials vend runs through
JCasbin, so the authz decision fires before any STS call:
  tenant_a vend s3://.../tenant_a/x (own)   -> passed authz (500 at STS: no creds loaded, expected)
  tenant_b vend s3://.../tenant_b/x (own)   -> passed authz (500 at STS)
  tenant_a vend s3://.../tenant_b/x (cross)  -> HTTP 403 PERMISSION_DENIED  <-- authz deny
  tenant_b vend s3://.../tenant_a/x (cross)  -> HTTP 403 PERMISSION_DENIED  <-- authz deny, both dirs
Interpretation: a granted principal passes authz and proceeds to AssumeRole; an un-granted principal
is refused before any STS call, both directions. UC analogue of the Lakekeeper tenant_a -> 404 proof.

=========================================================================================
PART B. Full L5 on live AWS (account <ACCT>, us-east-1). Minimal keyless throwaway resources
(one S3 bucket + one vend role); UC ran under the caller's ambient session (default provider chain);
role trust hardened to REQUIRE the UC-generated external-id (sts:ExternalId condition). All resources
torn down after the run.

  == storage credential (real role) -> UC generated external_id=<uc-external-id>
  == role trust hardened to require that external-id (confused-deputy pin)
  == two external locations (s3://<bucket>/tenant_a, /tenant_b), per-tenant grants
  SUMMARY: passed=6 failed=0
  PASS: tenant_a vended real downscoped creds (ASIA<redacted>)     <- positive vend, downscoped STS
  PASS: tenant_a DENIED for tenant_b (authz)                       <- cross-tenant vend deny
  PASS: tenant_b DENIED for tenant_a (authz)                       <- both directions
  PASS: vended creds READ own prefix (tenant_a/) OK                <- downscope allows own prefix
  PASS: vended creds DENIED on cross prefix (tenant_b/) AccessDenied  <- downscope refuses other prefix
  ALL L5 CHECKS PASSED (UC OSS 0.5.0 per-tenant downscoped + external-id-pinned + authz-gated vending)

=========================================================================================
PART C. Full end-to-end THROUGH SPARK on live AWS (the whole stack on UC alone). Spark 4.0.1 +
unitycatalog-spark_4.0_2.13:0.5.0 + delta-spark 4.0.1 + hadoop-aws 3.4.1. Two external Delta tables
seeded to S3 under per-tenant prefixes (tenant_a/events, tenant_b/events), registered in UC as EXTERNAL
DELTA tables under the per-tenant external locations; tenant_a granted SELECT on ta_events only, tenant_b
on tb_events only. A Spark job carrying each tenant's UC token (as a per-tenant Connect server would inject
it server-side) reads via the UC Spark connector: UC loadTable authz -> downscoped credential vend ->
executor reads the tenant's Delta files in S3.

  token=tenant_a:  read unity.t.ta_events -> 2 rows [ALLOWED]      read unity.t.tb_events -> 403 PERMISSION_DENIED
  token=tenant_b:  read unity.t.ta_events -> 403 PERMISSION_DENIED  read unity.t.tb_events -> 2 rows [ALLOWED]

A Spark query authenticated per-tenant reaches ONLY that tenant's data (authz grant + downscoped vend +
executor S3 read) and is denied the other tenant's at the catalog, both directions, end to end on UC OSS
alone. Scope: L1 (Envoy mTLS ingress routing) and per-tenant k8s executor-POD separation (part of L3) are
catalog-independent and were demonstrated on the Lakekeeper stack; here executors are local threads, so the
DATA read is isolated by the vend while pod-level separation is the same k8s layer. The catalog-integrated
path, token custody (L2, at config), per-principal authz (L4), and downscoped vend + storage scoping (L5),
is proven end to end through Spark on UC.

Addendum (OIDC front door, tokens UC actually issued). The Part C run above used internal-issuer JWTs
signed with UC's own key (the mechanism UC's integration tests use). Re-run with tokens obtained through
UC's real OAuth2 token-exchange: a mock OIDC IdP (static JWKS, served on a shared docker network) issues an
external JWT per tenant; UC validates it against server.allowed-issuers + server.audiences, fetches the IdP's
JWKS via OIDC discovery, and mints its own access token; that UC-issued token drives the same Spark isolation.
Result identical, both directions: tenant_a reads only ta_events (tb_events 403), tenant_b reads only tb_events
(ta_events 403). So the per-tenant isolation holds with tokens UC itself issued through its OIDC front door,
not just self-signed internal ones. Scripts: scratchpad/idp_gen.py + exchange.py.

=========================================================================================
Verified in v0.5.0 source: vending gated by @AuthorizeExpression(VEND_TABLE_CREDENTIAL)
(READ->SELECT, READ_WRITE->SELECT+MODIFY); AwsPolicyGenerator builds the inline session policy scoped
to the exact prefix; AwsCredentialVendor passes AssumeRoleRequest.externalId(). Honest residual gaps
(v0.5.0): per-principal L4 is NOT expressible on UC's Iceberg-REST path (metastore-OWNER, all-or-nothing,
read-only/UniForm-only), only the UC-native plugin; authz is off by default; no RLS/column masking in OSS;
JCasbin is single/non-thread-safe under concurrent policy reload; standing up per-principal auth required
patching two 0.5.0 authz bugs (multi-frame body parsing; missing GET /permissions authz expression).
Scripts: scratchpad/proof_uc_l4.sh (Part A), scratchpad/proof_uc_L5_aws.sh (Part B),
scratchpad/uc_e2e_provision.sh + seed_delta.py + uc_isolation.py (Part C).
